description:
Details ------------------------------------------------------- Name:Remote MPT for New Transfer Students Description:Math Placement Test offering at Hunter College for incoming transfer students. The exam will be conducted remotely with a proctor. Students must present valid physical (non-electronic) photo identification to test. Students can test remotely using the following operating systems: MacOS or Windows. A webcam, smartphone (for environment check only), mic and strong internet connection are required to test. Note, the following devices cannot be used for testing: Chromebook OS, iPad, Smartphone, Kindle, and Tablets. Students must know their CUNY Blackboard login credentials. Category:Testing Center Events Host(s):Testing Center Contact Phone: Contact Email:testing@hunter.cuny.edu Location:Virtual Event Address:The session will be conducted via Zoom. Be sure to respond to the registration confirmation email and provide us with the type of operating system you will use to test. We will then provide you with the ZOOM link for the exam. Be ready to present valid physical (non-electronic) photo identification. Additional Details:What you need to know:
  1. Arrival: Please arrive at the exam report-in time provided with the ZOOM meeting link.
  2. The exam location: The session will be conducted via Zoom. Be sure to respond to the registration confirmation email and provide us with the type of operating system you will use to test. We will then provide you with the ZOOM link for the exam. Be ready to present valid physical (non-electronic) photo identification.
  3. What to bring: A Valid Physical (non-electronic) Photo ID (e.g. passport, state ID, school photo ID)
    4. Calculators and scrap paper are not allowed
  4. Where to find a sample test questions: Log in to Blackboard.
    5. On the left side panel, conduct an Organization Search for Hunter Math Placement Test Prep. Click on the Organization ID, HTR01_org_math_placement_test_prep, click +Enroll, submit and OK. Be sure to view READ THIS FIRST
summary: Meeting Scheduled:Remote MPT for New Transfer Students
